    {'text': 'When thou passest through the waters, I will be with thee; and through the rivers, they shall not overflow thee.', 'reference': 'Isaiah 43:2'},
    {'text': 'It is good for me that I have been afflicted; that I might learn thy statutes.', 'reference': 'Psalm 119:71'},
    {'text': 'I press toward the mark for the prize of the high calling of God in Christ Jesus.', 'reference': 'Philippians 3:14'},
    {'text': 'Lift up your heads, O ye gates; and be ye lift up, ye everlasting doors; and the King of glory shall come in.', 'reference': 'Psalm 24:7'},
    {'text': 'But the wisdom that is from above is first pure, then peaceable, gentle, and easy to be intreated, full of mercy and good fruits.', 'reference': 'James 3:17'},
    {'text': 'He hath made every thing beautiful in his time: also he hath set the world in their heart.', 'reference': 'Ecclesiastes 3:11'},
    {'text': 'Sing unto the Lord a new song, and his praise from the end of the earth.', 'reference': 'Isaiah 42:10'},

    // Day 231-240
    {'text': 'The Lord will give strength unto his people; the Lord will bless his people with peace.', 'reference': 'Psalm 29:11'},
    {'text': 'If ye then, being evil, know how to give good gifts unto your children, how much more shall your Father which is in heaven give good things to them that ask him?', 'reference': 'Matthew 7:11'},
